cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper discusses the practical estimation of the maximum size of a neural network given a training data set, which is a topic related to machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the capacity of neural network architectures, which is related to neural network engineering, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the estimation of neural network capacity requirements for a given dataset and labeling, which is related to artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the application of neural networks in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the consequences of sizing the network wrongly, which is related to control systems and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
